# CODEOWNERS
# -----------
# Auto-assigns reviewers when matching paths are changed in a PR.
# GitHub enforces review requirements when this file is committed to the default branch
# and branch protection is configured with "Require review from Code Owners".
#
# HOW TO ADOPT THIS TEMPLATE
# ---------------------------
# Replace every @your-org/* placeholder with your actual GitHub team or username.
# Create teams in GitHub: Settings → Teams, then grant repo access.
#
# Suggested team structure (create these before your first enterprise engagement):
#   @your-org/platform-team    — Tech Lead + senior engineers (global fallback)
#   @your-org/tech-leads       — Architecture decisions, ADRs, specs, changelog
#   @your-org/privacy-team     — DPO; required before any GDPR/LGPD assessment
#   @your-org/ai-governance    — AI Governance Lead; required before enabling HOTL
#   @your-org/security-team    — Security Lead; required before SOC 2 audit
#   @your-org/sre-team         — SRE Lead + on-call engineers
#   @your-org/devops-team      — CI/CD pipelines, infrastructure, deploy scripts
#
# Run this to list current contributors after adopting:
#   gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/collaborators
#
# Role index (update when your team grows):
#   Platform / Tech Lead      → @your-org/platform-team
#   DPO (Data Protection)     → @your-org/privacy-team   ← assign before enterprise engagement
#   Security Lead             → @your-org/security-team  ← assign before SOC 2
#   AI Governance Lead        → @your-org/ai-governance
#   SRE Lead                  → @your-org/sre-team
#   DevOps Lead               → @your-org/devops-team

# ── Global fallback ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All files not matched by a more-specific rule below.
*                                    @your-org/platform-team

